<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFFFFC0FF71FC00FC74FBBE" blockId="23.[151,1436,906,1041]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
The diagnosis is covered in the 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFFFFC0FE11FC01FD88FC42" authorityName="Borth &amp; Kons" authorityYear="2021" box="[503,629,978,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afrikana">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFFFFC0FE11FC01FD88FC42" box="[503,629,978,1004]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">E. afrikana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
description and under 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFFFFC0FC92FC01FBC8FC42" authorityName="Brou, Klem, Zaspel &amp; Zilli" authorityYear="2017" box="[884,1077,979,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="steppingstonia">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFFFFC0FC92FC01FBC8FC42" box="[884,1077,979,1004]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">E. steppingstonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(above). All three known specimens were collected on the 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFFFFC0FE28FC25FDD7FBBF" box="[462,554,1015,1041]" name="Vanuatu" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Vanuatu</collectingCountry>
